# Scenario 8: Branch Policies and PR Enforcement

## 🎯 Objective
Protect the `main` branch by requiring minimum reviewers, build validation, and comment resolution before merging.

## 📋 Prerequisites
- Azure DevOps project with Azure Repos
- At least one pipeline created

## 🛠️ Step-by-Step Lab

### Step 1: Set Minimum Reviewers Policy via CLI

```bash
# Get project ID
az devops project show --project "MyProject" --query id -o tsv

# Get repository ID
az repos show --repository MyRepo --query id -o tsv

# Create minimum reviewers policy
az repos policy approver-count create \
  --allow-downvotes false \
  --blocking true \
  --branch main \
  --creator-vote-counts false \
  --enabled true \
  --minimum-approver-count 2 \
  --repository-id <REPO_ID> \
  --reset-on-source-push true
```

### Step 2: Set Build Validation Policy via CLI

```bash
# Get pipeline definition ID
az pipelines show --name "MyBuildPipeline" --query id -o tsv

# Create build validation policy
az repos policy build create \
  --blocking true \
  --branch main \
  --build-definition-id <PIPELINE_ID> \
  --display-name "PR Build Validation" \
  --enabled true \
  --manual-queue-only false \
  --queue-on-source-update true \
  --repository-id <REPO_ID> \
  --valid-duration 720
```

### Step 3: Require Comment Resolution via CLI

```bash
az repos policy comment-required create \
  --blocking true \
  --branch main \
  --enabled true \
  --repository-id <REPO_ID>
```

### Step 4: Require Work Item Linking

```bash
az repos policy work-item-linking create \
  --blocking true \
  --branch main \
  --enabled true \
  --repository-id <REPO_ID>
```

### Step 5: View All Policies on a Branch

```bash
az repos policy list \
  --branch main \
  --repository-id <REPO_ID> \
  --output table
```

### Step 6: Create a PR to Test Policies

```bash
# Create a feature branch
git checkout -b feature/add-login
git add .
git commit -m "feat: add login page AB#42"
git push origin feature/add-login

# Create PR via CLI
az repos pr create \
  --title "Add Login Feature" \
  --description "Implements user login. Closes AB#42" \
  --source-branch feature/add-login \
  --target-branch main \
  --reviewers "jane.doe@company.com" "john.smith@company.com"
```

## ✅ Expected Output / Answer

```
PR #7: Add Login Feature
Status: Active

Policies:
  ✅ Build Validation       PASS  (Pipeline ran successfully)
  ⏳ Minimum Reviewers      1/2   (Need 1 more approval)
  ⏳ Comment Resolution     0/1   (1 unresolved comment)
  ✅ Work Item Linking      PASS  (AB#42 linked)

  ❌ Not ready to merge — 2 policies blocking
```

After all policies met:
```
  ✅ Build Validation       PASS
  ✅ Minimum Reviewers      2/2
  ✅ Comment Resolution     PASS
  ✅ Work Item Linking      PASS
  🟢 Ready to merge!
```

